n faculty approved learning objectives  and include passing the NBME Subject Exam in each discipline M  Course Breakdown M  Year     weeks General Description of the M  Year The M  year includes    weeks of selectives  four  four week rotations  plus    weeks of electives  Eight weeks of discretionary time are available which students may use for preparation for USMLE Step   CS and CK  residency interviews or vacation  Students must pass Step   CS and CK of the United States Medical Licensing Examination  USMLE  in order to graduate  A mock Step   CS standardized patient experience is offered at the beginning of the M  year to prepare students for the clinical skills part of the Step   examination Individual electives in the M  year are either two or four weeks in duration  Rockford students may also choose elective experiences at other U S  medical schools and or to study abroad  The College of Medicine at Rockford is one of the few U S  medical schools belonging to the International Network of Community Oriented Educational Institutions for Health Sciences  Students are encouraged to see and experience medicine in varying contexts  including Third World settings via fellowships in cooperation with Network institutions and others Education MD Admissions Rockford Interviews MD Curriculum Campus Specific Programs Clinician Executive Medicine Program  CE MED James Scholar Program for Independent Study Rural Medical Education  RMED  Program Curriculum by Year M  Year M  Year M  and M  Years Psychiatry Clerkship Course Management Blackboard Exams Benware Course Evaluations Visiting Students Medical Education and Evaluation MD Student Services and Support Student Affairs Staff Academic Skills Step   Resources Housing Computing Registrar Career Services Scholarship Opportunities Student Financial Planning Student Health and Wellness MD Student Life Rockford Resources Student Organizations Parking   Transportation Diversity Educational Policies Master of Science in Medical